Q25.8(2): The last part of the answer did not make sense - why would you boil both 1/2 cups of water separately?
Q25.8(3): I don't know "check in link" but then again, I am one of the very few people *not* on Facebook (and never having been on it) so this is probably common sense to everyone else!
Q25.8(4): We don't know what kind of "potion" this is, nor what it consists of, to make a good judgment about the solution (and why there would be a glare)
Q25.8(5): I don't understand the 'concept' of using Instagram because I'm not on it!  So not sure how one goes to the home page... but i do think this is common knowledge.

Q25.8(8): you would need to attach it/sew it after rolling it, but sure this could work
Q25.8(11): which knobs? Would have needed more details before deciding if this made sense
Q25.8(12): I know Nikon cameras (and still have one!) but I'm unfamiliar with a "b500" model.  A cloth over the lens would probably work, although most lens have round plastic covers, attached with a leather strap, that fit over them to protect them.
Q25.8(13): underspecified: You would also need to make sure you had the correct syntax, were using the language of the recipient, and that the recipient were able to see the paper

Q25.8(21): the use of "strangle" here was odd.  "Suffocate" perhaps, and also you are cutting of the oxygen, not using it's own smoke against it.  But putting a cup over it upside down would still achieve the end of cutting off O2.  Concave is redundant perhaps?  (all cups are concave on one side?...)

Q25.8(27): I understood the Q&A, but neither the purpose nor procedure made sense to me.  Yes a file could probably achieve this, but it sounds like abuse!
Q25.8(30): it would help to know what *kind* of ornament, if "desk ornament" were specified, because not all ornaments (lawn ornaments, Christmas tree ornament) would be well used as desk ornamentation.
